      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>William H. Twenhofel (1875-1957), Ph.D. Yale (1912), is regarded as the patriarch of sedimentary geology. Twenhofel, who was a member of the National Research Council, retired in 1945 from an illustrious academic career at the University of Wisconsin, Madison. Twenhofel cofounded the Journal of Sedimentary Petrology, now the Journal of Sedimentary Research.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>Topographic maps of Anticosti Island, Quebec, and surrounding areas, along with typed copies of his field notes. Also, faunal lists and locality information from other expeditions including ones to Kansas and Texas.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
